28/02/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police on Friday (February 26th) arrested three people suspected of involvement in the systematic execution of thousands of Muslims in Srebrenica during the 1992-1995 conflict in BiH. 
The chief prosecutor announced that Vlastimir Golijan, 35, Zoran Goronja, 38, and Stanko Savanovic, 42 -- all former soldiers in the Bosnian Serb army -- were directly involved in the execution of men and boys from Srebrenica in July 1995. 
(Court of BiH website, AP, Fena - 26/02/10)
